Lita:  An Extreme Comeback

This home made, yet high quality video recorded on PREMIUM GRADE SONY VHS video tape
shows Lita's WWE television appearances between September 15th, 2003 [Her WWE Return]
all the way up to [TAPE NOT YET COMPLETE]

Questions?  Comments?  Contact me at TrishSite@aol.com.  AOL IM:  TrishSite

The VHS video cassette includes ALL of the following dates and events:

Date Event Description
September 15th, 2003 Raw [SpikeTV] Lita makes her return to WWE after more than a year when she comes to the aid of a distressed Trish Stratus who is receiving a post match beating at the hands of Molly Holly and Gail Kim.
     
September 21st, 2003 Unforgiven [PPV] Lita teams with Trish Stratus to take on the duo of Molly Holly and Gail Kim in a tag match.
     
September 22nd, 2003 Raw [SpikeTV] Trish & Lita solidify their position as the new dominant force in the women's division on Raw as they defeat Molly & Gail for the second night in a row.
     
September 29th, 2003 Raw [SpikeTV] Gail & Molly attack Lita, Trish comes to Lita's aid, Victoria attacks Trish and both Lita and Trish get laid out by Gail, Molly & Victoria.  Short segment to set up a future feud.
     
October 4th, 2003 Confidential [SpikeTV] We take a look at Lita's new autobiography as well as what it took for her to make her way back to the ring after suffering  a severe neck injury that kept her out of action for over a year.
     
October 6th, 2003 Raw [SpikeTV] Lita gets the victory over Gail Kim while the Women's Champion Molly Holly watches on from the announce position.
     
October 13th, 2003 Raw [SpikeTV] Lita participates in a 6-Diva tag match.  Participants are Lita, Trish, Ivory vs. Molly, Gail and Victoria.  Lita's team gets the victory.
     
October 20th, 2003 Raw [SpikeTV] Trish teamed with Lita to battle Victoria & Molly.  With the help of Steven Richards, Victoria gets the pin over Trish for the victory of her team.  After a post-match attack, Lita is saved by Christian.
     
October 27th, 2003 Raw [SpikeTV] In the locker room, Trish and Lita discuss Chris Jericho's pursuit of Trish and how Lita thinks Jericho and Christian are up to something.  Lita searches out Christian and asks him what's going on, he tells her that he has feelings for her.  Later in a fatal four way match for the #1 contendership, Lita gets the victory and a shot at the title come Survivor Series.
     
November 3rd, 2003 Raw [SpikeTV] After Terri interviews Molly, she is attacked by the Women's Champion.  Lita comes to Terri's aid, only to be double teamed by Molly and Gail Kim until she is laid out in the middle of the ring.  Later in the locker room, Christian shows his concern for Lita as the trainers tend to Lita.
     
November 8th, 2003 Confidential [SpikeTV] A behind the scenes look at one of Lita's Autobiography signings through the eyes of Lita's fans and Lita herself.
     
November 10th, 2003 Raw [SpikeTV] Lita & Terri team up against Molly Holly & Gail Kim.  Terri, not a seasoned wrestler, was taken advantage of most of the match until Lita is tagged in and makes Molly & Gail pay for their abuse of the Raw interviewer.  However a double team and extra leverage with the help of the ring ropes gets Molly the pin over Lita.  Post match, Gail and Molly destroy Terri.
     
November 16th, 2003 Survivor Series [PPV] Lita comes close to making her return complete by defeating Molly Holly for the Women's Championship.  It just didn't come to be.  When Molly removed the turnbuckle padding, Lita found herself face first into the exposed steel to allow Molly the win, walking out of Survivor Series with her title.
     
November 17th, 2003 Raw [SpikeTV] The return of Jericho's Highlight Reel had Lita and Matt Hardy reunited.  However when a match was made teaming the two, Hardy would leave Lita's corner, abandoning her to be beaten by the team of Molly & Eric Bischoff.  Stipulations had it that Lita was now fired from WWE as a result of the loss but because Bischoff owed Christian a favor, Lita was reinstated at the request of the so-called "CLB".
     
November 24th, 2003 Raw [SpikeTV] Eric Bischoff's Raw Roulette Reel forced Lita into the first ever women's steel cage match with Victoria.  When Lita had the match nearly won by escaping the cage through the door, Matt Hardy came down to slam it in her face, allowing Victoria to escape for victory.  Hardy entered the ring, seemingly to assault Lita until Christian came to her aid.
     
December 1st, 2003 Raw [SpikeTV] Lita & Trish talk in the back.  Trish reveals her strong feelings for Jericho.  Later in a match where he would face Matt Hardy, Lita escorted Christian to the ring.  When Lita was attacked from behind by Molly Holly, Christian would be a gentleman and help her to her feet.  However in the locker room, Jericho & Christian reveal that their pursuit of Trish & Lita respectively is nothing more than a friendly bet of who can sleep with the girl of his choice first.
     
December 8th, 2003 Raw [SpikeTV] Trish & Lita refuse to accept an apology from Jericho & Christian.  Later, the women team up against Molly & Victoria, only to lose the match on account of Matt Hardy.
     
December 14th, 2003 Heat [SpikeTV] A video package showing all the events leading up to the 'Battle of the Sexes' event is shown before interviewer Terri speaks with Trish and Lita prior to the event.
     
December 14th, 2003 Armageddon [PPV] 'Battle of the Sexes' where Trish & Lita team against Jericho and Christian ends when Jericho shows a soft side for Trish as Christian takes advantage and rolls Trish up for the win.
     
December 15th, 2003 Raw [SpikeTV] 'Battle of the Sexes II' shows us Lita & Trish vs. Christian & Jericho.  The match ends with Christian rolling up Trish while she was distracted by Jericho's unexpected kindness.
3:12:11    
December 29th, 2003 Raw [SpikeTV] Lita, Trish and Stacy team up to take on Victoria, Molly and Jackie Gayda in a Happy Holidays match.
     
January 10th, 2004 Confidential [SpikeTV] 12 WWE Superstars come together to create a CD entitled 'WWE Originals' with tracks written specifically for the performer by Jim Johnstone.  Those involved include John Cena, Booker T, Rey Mysterio, Trish Stratus, Lita, Chris Jericho, The Dudleys, Rikishi, Stacy Keibler and more.
     
January 12th, 2004 Raw [SpikeTV] Trish & Lita team to compete against Jazz and Molly.  When Theodore Long distracted Trish, Jazz was able to grab Trish's tights and roll her up for the victory.
     
January 19th, 2004 Raw [SpikeTV] Lita goes one on one with Jazz.  Theodore Long distracts Lita, allowing Jazz to roll up Lita with illegal leverage, using Lita's pants and belt to hold her on mat for the three count.
     
January 26th, 2004 Raw [SpikeTV] Victoria & Lita team up to do battle with Molly Holly and Jazz.  Victoria pins Molly for the second night in a row for the victory.
     

E-Mail: TrishSite@aol.com | AOL Instant Message: TrishSite | Web Site:  TrishStratus.8k.com

More Details:  The tape does have a few minor imperfections,
however the quality of the video becomes better and better as the tape progresses.
I made an effort to improve the quality of the cable signal throughout the making of the video.
